(40, 12, 30, 62, 2, 19, 19, 'He that is not with me is against me', 'Divisive Nature of Allegiance', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of division based on allegiance. Matthew highlights that those not with Jesus are against him, while 1 John indicates that those who left were never truly part of the community.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
