(40, 20, 1, 40, 13, 47, 47, 'kingdom of heaven', 'Kingdom of Heaven Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of the kingdom of heaven through metaphors. The householder hiring laborers and the net gathering fish illustrate the inclusive and active nature of God''s kingdom.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 1, 22, 8, 11, 12, 'vineyard', 'Vineyard Imagery Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a vineyard managed by keepers or laborers. The householder in Matthew hires laborers for his vineyard, while Solomon lets out his vineyard to keepers, highlighting a shared theme of stewardship and labor in relation to vineyards.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 1, 58, 13, 21, 21, NULL, 'Work in the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor and divine purpose. Both passages emphasize the importance of working to fulfill God''s will, as seen in the laborers hired for the vineyard and the call to be made perfect in good works.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 1, 23, 5, 1, 2, 'vineyard', 'Connection of Vineyard Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a vineyard, representing care and expectation. The householder in Matthew actively hires laborers for his vineyard, paralleling the beloved in Isaiah who cultivates his vineyard with great effort.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 1, 43, 15, 1, 1, 'vineyard', 'Connection of Vineyard Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a vineyard, with Matthew describing a householder hiring laborers for his vineyard and John referring to Jesus as the true vine. This connection highlights the agricultural imagery used to convey spiritual truths about the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 1, 46, 15, 58, 58, 'labourers into his vineyard', 'Labor in the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor in both passages. Matthew 20:1 speaks of hiring laborers for a vineyard, while 1 Corinthians 15:58 encourages steadfastness in the work of the Lord, affirming that such labor is meaningful.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 2, 2, 19, 5, 6, 'agreed with the labourers', 'Labor and Covenant Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of agreement and reward for obedience. In Matthew, the laborers agree for a wage, while in Exodus, obedience to God''s covenant brings a special status and reward.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 2, 5, 5, 27, 30, 'agreed with the labourers', 'Labor and Obedience Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of agreement and obedience. In Matthew, the laborers agree to work for a wage, while in Deuteronomy, the people agree to hear and do the Lord''s commands.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 2, 9, 2, 18, 18, NULL, 'Service and Labor in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of service, as both passages depict individuals engaged in labor for a greater purpose. In Matthew, the laborers are sent into the vineyard, while Samuel is described as ministering before the Lord, emphasizing dedication to their respective tasks.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
