(40, 20, 3, 40, 20, 6, 7, 'standing idle', 'Idle Workers in the Vineyard', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of workers standing idle in the marketplace. The repetition of ''standing idle'' highlights the urgency of hiring laborers for the vineyard, illustrating the owner''s concern for those without work.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 3, 41, 15, 25, 25, 'the third hour', 'Connection of the Third Hour', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the third hour. In Matthew, it marks the time when laborers are called, while in Mark, it denotes the moment of Jesus'' crucifixion.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 3, 44, 2, 15, 15, 'the third hour', 'Connection through the Third Hour', 'Both passages emphasize the ''third hour,'' linking the timing of events. In Matthew, it marks the moment of calling workers, while in Acts, it denotes the time of day during the Pentecost event.', 'keyword', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
