(40, 21, 25, 40, 3, 1, 12, 'the baptism of John, whence was it?', 'Connection of John the Baptist''s Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of John''s baptism and its divine origin. In Matthew 21:25, the question of whether John''s baptism is ''from heaven'' or ''of men'' directly relates to his role as depicted in Matthew 3:1-12, where he is introduced as a prophetic figure preparing the way for Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 42, 20, 5, 5, 'If we shall say, From heaven;', 'Connection of Reasoning about John', 'Both passages emphasize the reasoning of the individuals regarding the source of John''s baptism. They pose a similar rhetorical question about believing John, highlighting a shared concern about authority.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 43, 1, 15, 15, 'believe him', 'Connection of John the Baptist''s Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of John the Baptist''s role in relation to Jesus. Matthew questions the divine authority of John''s baptism, while John affirms John''s witness to Jesus'' preeminence.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 43, 3, 18, 18, 'believe him', 'Belief and Condemnation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and its consequences. Both passages emphasize the importance of believing in divine authority, as seen in the questioning of John''s baptism and the condemnation for not believing in the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 40, 11, 7, 15, 'from heaven, or of men?', 'Connection Between John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of John the Baptist as a prophet. In Matthew 21:25, the question of John''s authority is raised, while Matthew 11:7-15 affirms his prophetic role and greatness. This connection highlights the importance of recognizing John''s message and authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 41, 6, 20, 20, 'fear the people', 'Fear of John the Baptist', 'This connection highlights the fear surrounding John the Baptist. Both passages emphasize the respect and recognition of John as a prophet, influencing the actions and perceptions of those around him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 40, 11, 9, 9, 'John as a prophet', 'Connection of Prophetic Recognition', 'This connection highlights the recognition of John as a prophet in both passages. In Matthew 21:26, the people''s view of John as a prophet is emphasized, while Matthew 11:9 affirms John''s prophetic status and suggests he is more than just a prophet.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 40, 14, 5, 5, NULL, 'Fear of the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the people regarding John as a prophet. This connection highlights how public perception influences the actions of leaders in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 43, 5, 35, 35, 'John as a prophet', 'Connection Between John and Light', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of John as a prophet and a source of light. The reference to John as a prophet in Matthew aligns with his depiction as a ''burning and shining light'' in John, highlighting his role in guiding others.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 23, 57, 11, 11, 'we fear the people', 'Fear of People and God', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear in both passages. Matthew discusses fearing the people regarding John the Baptist, while Isaiah questions whom the people have feared instead of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 41, 11, 32, 32, 'for all hold John as a prophet', 'Connection of Fear and Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the people regarding John the Baptist''s prophetic status. They highlight the common understanding that John was regarded as a prophet, which influenced the speakers'' responses.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 42, 20, 6, 6, 'Of men; we fear the people', 'Connection of Fear Regarding John', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the people regarding John as a prophet. They reflect the concern of the speakers about the consequences of declaring John''s authority.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 45, 1, 18, 22, 'by what authority I do these things', 'Authority and Knowledge of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority and knowledge of God. In Matthew, the refusal to acknowledge Jesus'' authority parallels Romans'' assertion that people suppress the truth about God, leading to a darkened understanding.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 53, 2, 9, 10, 'by what authority I do these things', 'Authority and Deception', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority and deception in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus'' authority is questioned, while in 2 Thessalonians, the coming figure operates with deception and false signs.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 23, 6, 10, 10, NULL, 'Understanding and Spiritual Blindness', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual blindness and lack of understanding. Both passages emphasize the inability to perceive truth, as seen in the leaders'' inability to discern Jesus'' authority and in Isaiah''s warning about the people''s hardened hearts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 23, 28, 9, 9, NULL, 'Understanding Authority and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding and authority in both passages. In Matthew, the inability to discern Jesus'' authority parallels Isaiah''s inquiry about who can truly grasp knowledge and doctrine.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 24, 8, 7, 9, 'We cannot tell', 'Wisdom and Authority Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of divine wisdom. In Matthew, the leaders fail to recognize Jesus'' authority, paralleling Jeremiah''s critique of the people''s ignorance of God''s judgment. This connection highlights the theme of spiritual blindness among those who should know better.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 39, 2, 6, 9, NULL, 'Authority and Knowledge in Leadership', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority and the expectation of truthfulness in leadership. In Matthew, Jesus challenges the religious leaders'' inability to recognize his authority, while Malachi emphasizes the importance of the priest''s role in keeping knowledge and truth. Both passages address the failures of leaders to uphold their responsibilities.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 40, 15, 14, 14, NULL, 'Authority and Blindness', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority and discernment. In both passages, Jesus addresses the failure of leaders to recognize true authority, suggesting that without proper insight, they lead others into error.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
