(40, 21, 32, 42, 7, 29, 30, 'believed him not', 'Response to John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize the contrasting responses to John the Baptist''s message. In Matthew, the publicans and harlots believed, while the Pharisees did not, which parallels Luke''s depiction of the publicans justifying God and the Pharisees rejecting his counsel.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
