(40, 22, 32, 42, 20, 37, 38, 'God is not the God of the dead, but of the living', 'Connection of Living God', 'Both passages emphasize that God is not the God of the dead, but of the living, highlighting the continuity of life in God''s relationship with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. This connection underscores the belief in resurrection and eternal life.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 32, 44, 7, 32, 32, 'the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob', 'Connection of God''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize God''s identity as the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, highlighting His relationship with the patriarchs. This connection underscores the continuity of God''s covenant with His people.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 32, 2, 3, 15, 16, NULL, 'Connection of God''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize God''s identity as ''the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.'' This connection highlights the continuity of God''s relationship with the patriarchs, affirming that He is a living God who is actively involved with His people.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 32, 58, 11, 16, 16, 'God is not the God of the dead', 'God of the Living', 'This connection highlights the theme of God being associated with the living, as seen in Matthew''s assertion that God is not the God of the dead. Hebrews emphasizes that God is not ashamed to be called their God, indicating a relationship with those who seek a heavenly country, reinforcing the idea of life beyond death.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
