(40, 22, 33, 42, 4, 22, 22, 'astonished at his doctrine', 'Astonishment at Jesus'' Words', 'This connection highlights the reaction of the crowd to Jesus'' teachings in both passages. Both verses emphasize the wonder and astonishment of the people at the gracious and authoritative nature of his words.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 33, 43, 7, 46, 46, 'astonished at his doctrine', 'Astonishment at Jesus'' Teaching', 'This connection highlights the impact of Jesus'' teaching on His audience. Both passages emphasize the extraordinary nature of His doctrine, leading to astonishment and recognition of His unique authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 34, 41, 12, 28, 31, 'the Pharisees had heard', 'Interaction with Religious Leaders', 'This connection highlights the engagement of Jesus with religious authorities. In both passages, the Pharisees and scribes are depicted as responding to Jesus'' teachings, showcasing a dialogue about the commandments.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 34, 40, 25, 3, 5, NULL, 'Preparedness and Wisdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of readiness and vigilance. Both passages emphasize the importance of being prepared, as seen in the wise taking oil for their lamps while the Pharisees gather to challenge Jesus, indicating a need for spiritual awareness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 34, 40, 12, 14, 14, 'the Pharisees had heard', 'Pharisees'' Opposition to Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the Pharisees'' growing hostility towards Jesus. In Matthew 22:34, their gathering indicates a strategic response to his teachings, while Matthew 12:14 shows their intent to destroy him.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 34, 23, 41, 5, 7, 'they were gathered together', 'Encouragement in Adversity', 'This connection highlights the theme of encouragement in the face of challenges. In both passages, there is a sense of gathering and support among individuals, whether it be the Pharisees coming together or the craftsmen encouraging one another.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 34, 43, 11, 47, 50, 'they were gathered together', 'Gathering of Religious Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of religious leaders in response to Jesus'' actions. In Matthew, the Pharisees gather after being silenced, while in John, they convene to discuss the implications of Jesus'' miracles.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 34, 44, 5, 24, 28, NULL, 'Confrontation with Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between religious authorities and those teaching in the name of Jesus. In Matthew, the Pharisees gather to confront Jesus after he silences the Sadducees, while in Acts, the high priest and council confront the apostles for teaching despite their commands.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 34, 44, 19, 23, 28, NULL, 'Conflict Over Worship', 'Both passages emphasize a conflict arising from differing beliefs about worship. In Matthew, the Pharisees gather to confront Jesus after a challenge to their authority, while in Acts, Demetrius rallies craftsmen against Paul for undermining the worship of Diana.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 35, 42, 7, 30, 30, 'lawyer', 'Rejection of God''s Counsel', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection of God''s counsel by religious leaders. In both passages, the actions of the lawyers reflect a challenge to divine authority, as seen in their questioning of Jesus and their refusal to accept baptism.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 35, 42, 10, 25, 37, 'which was a lawyer, asked him a question', 'Connection of Legal Inquiry', 'Both passages emphasize a lawyer asking Jesus a question about inheriting eternal life. This connection highlights the theme of legal interpretation and the nature of neighborly love as central to the discussion.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
