(40, 22, 35, 56, 3, 13, 13, 'lawyer', 'Connection of Legal Expertise', 'This connection highlights the role of lawyers in both passages. In Matthew, a lawyer questions Jesus, while in Titus, Zenas is referred to as a lawyer, indicating a shared theme of legal authority.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 35, 41, 10, 2, 2, 'tempting him', 'Temptation in Legal Questions', 'Both passages emphasize the act of tempting Jesus through legal inquiries. In Matthew, a lawyer poses a question, while in Mark, the Pharisees ask about divorce, both aiming to challenge him.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 36, 41, 12, 28, 33, 'which is the great commandment in the law?', 'Great Commandment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of loving God and neighbor. They present a unified teaching on the greatest commandments, highlighting love as central to the law.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 36, 40, 5, 19, 20, 'great commandment in the law', 'Connection of Commandments and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the importance of commandments in both passages. In Matthew 22:36, the question of the greatest commandment leads to the emphasis on obeying and teaching all commandments in Matthew 5:19-20, linking righteousness to adherence to the law.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 36, 42, 11, 42, 42, 'great commandment in the law', 'Connection of Commandment and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love and judgment in the law. Matthew highlights the great commandment, while Luke critiques the Pharisees for neglecting judgment and love of God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
