(40, 22, 46, 40, 21, 27, 27, 'neither durst any man from that day forth ask him any more questions', 'Authority and Questioning Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the inability of others to answer Jesus. In Matthew 21:27, the response of ''We cannot tell'' reflects a similar theme in Matthew 22:46, where no one could answer him. This connection highlights the authority of Jesus in both instances.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
