(40, 28, 17, 19, 45, 11, 11, NULL, 'Worship and Kingship Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of worship towards a figure of authority. In Matthew, some worship Jesus, while Psalms speaks of worshiping the king as the Lord.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 17, 40, 16, 28, 28, 'some doubted', 'Worship and Doubt in Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of witnesses to significant events involving the Son of man. In Matthew 28:17, some worship while others doubt, paralleling the anticipation of seeing the Son of man in Matthew 16:28.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 17, 40, 28, 9, 9, 'worshipped him', 'Worship and Doubt in Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of worship towards Jesus after his resurrection. In Matthew 28:9, the women worship him, while in Matthew 28:17, some worship him but also express doubt.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 17, 43, 5, 23, 23, 'worshipped him', 'Worship and Honor of the Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of honoring the Son. In Matthew, the act of worship signifies recognition of Jesus'' divine authority, while John emphasizes that honoring the Son is equivalent to honoring the Father.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 17, 46, 15, 6, 6, 'but some doubted', 'Doubt and Witnesses of Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of doubt among witnesses of the resurrected Christ. Both passages mention the presence of some who doubted or have ''fallen asleep,'' indicating a shared experience of uncertainty among those who encountered Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 18, 43, 3, 35, 35, 'All power is given unto me', 'Authority of the Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority given to Jesus. Both passages emphasize that all power and all things are entrusted to Him.', 'theme', 0.944, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 18, 60, 3, 22, 22, 'All power is given unto me', 'Authority of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Jesus, with Matthew 28:18 stating that ''All power is given unto me'' and 1 Peter 3:22 noting that ''angels and authorities and powers being made subject unto him.'' This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s supreme power over all realms.', 'theme', 0.7899999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 18, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'All power is given unto me', 'Authority of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Jesus. In Matthew 28:18, Jesus declares, ''All power is given unto me,'' while in Matthew 11:27, he states that ''All things are delivered unto me of my Father.'' This connection highlights the divine authority and relationship between the Father and the Son.', 'theme', 0.692, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 18, 49, 1, 20, 22, 'All power is given unto me', 'Authority of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Jesus, with Matthew stating that ''All power is given unto me'' and Ephesians describing Him as ''Far above all principality, and power.'' This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s supreme power and position over all things.', 'theme', 0.643, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 18, 58, 2, 8, 8, 'All power is given unto me', 'Authority and Subjection Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority given to Jesus, as seen in both passages. Matthew emphasizes Jesus'' power in heaven and earth, while Hebrews discusses all things being put in subjection under him.', 'theme', 0.622, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 18, 27, 7, 13, 14, 'All power is given unto me', 'Authority and Dominion Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the granting of power and dominion. Matthew 28:18 states that all power is given to Jesus, while Daniel 7:14 describes the Son of man receiving dominion and a kingdom.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 18, 46, 15, 27, 27, 'All power is given unto me', 'Authority of Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s authority. Both passages emphasize that all power and authority are given to Jesus, with Matthew stating that ''All power is given unto me'' and 1 Corinthians affirming that ''all things are put under him.''', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 19, 41, 16, 15, 16, 'baptizing them in the name of the Father', 'Commission to Preach and Baptize', 'Both passages emphasize the command to go and teach or preach to all nations and creatures. They highlight the importance of baptism as part of the process of salvation.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 19, 44, 2, 38, 39, 'baptizing them in the name of', 'Baptism and Holy Spirit Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of baptism and the reception of the Holy Spirit. Matthew 28:19 instructs to baptize in the name of the Father, Son, and Holy Ghost, while Acts 2:38 highlights baptism in the name of Jesus Christ and the gift of the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 19, 44, 1, 8, 8, 'all nations', 'Commission to Witness', 'Both passages emphasize the call to reach all nations. Matthew 28:19 instructs to teach and baptize, while Acts 1:8 highlights being witnesses to the uttermost part of the earth.', 'theme', 0.8739999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 19, 42, 24, 47, 48, 'all nations', 'Commission to All Nations', 'Both passages emphasize the mission to teach and preach among all nations. Matthew focuses on baptizing in the name of the Father, Son, and Holy Ghost, while Luke highlights preaching repentance and remission of sins.', 'theme', 0.7899999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 19, 23, 49, 6, 6, 'teach all nations', 'Connection of Salvation to All Nations', 'Both passages emphasize the mission to reach all nations. Matthew 28:19''s call to teach all nations aligns with Isaiah 49:6''s declaration of being a light to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.6779999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 19, 48, 3, 27, 27, 'baptizing them in the name', 'Baptism and Identity in Christ', 'This connection highlights the act of baptism as a means of entering into a relationship with Christ. Both passages emphasize the significance of baptism in the believer''s identity and mission.', 'theme', 0.6639999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 19, 45, 6, 3, 4, 'baptizing them in the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism and New Life', 'This connection highlights the significance of baptism in both passages. Matthew 28:19 emphasizes baptizing in the name of the Father, Son, and Holy Ghost, while Romans 6:3-4 explains that baptism into Jesus Christ signifies participation in his death and resurrection, leading to newness of life.', 'theme', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 20, 23, 41, 10, 10, 'I am with you alway', 'Presence of God in Both Passages', 'Both passages emphasize God''s promise of presence and support. Matthew 28:20 states, ''I am with you alway,'' while Isaiah 41:10 reassures, ''I am with thee.'' This connection highlights the theme of divine companionship.', 'theme', 0.8459999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 20, 6, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'God''s Presence and Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize God''s promise of presence and support. Matthew 28:20 assures believers of Jesus'' continual presence, while Joshua 1:5 reinforces God''s commitment to be with Joshua, ensuring he will not be forsaken.', 'theme', 0.671, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 20, 44, 18, 9, 10, 'I am with you alway', 'Presence of God in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize God''s promise of presence and protection in ministry. Matthew assures believers of His constant presence, while Acts shows God reassuring Paul of His presence and safety in speaking out.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 20, 43, 14, 18, 23, 'I am with you alway', 'Presence and Commandment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of keeping commandments and the promise of Jesus'' presence. Matthew highlights Jesus'' assurance of being with his followers, while John speaks of Jesus manifesting himself to those who love him and keep his words.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 20, 19, 46, 7, 7, 'I am with you alway', 'Presence of God', 'Both passages emphasize the continual presence of God with His people. Matthew 28:20 assures believers of Christ''s presence ''even unto the end of the world,'' while Psalms 46:7 declares, ''The Lord of hosts is with us.''', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 20, 1, 39, 2, 3, 'I am with you alway', 'Presence of the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of the Lord with individuals, highlighting divine support and prosperity. In Matthew, Jesus assures His continual presence, while in Genesis, the Lord''s presence with Joseph leads to his success.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 28, 20, 62, 2, 3, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Commandments and Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of keeping commandments as a sign of knowing Christ. Matthew highlights the command to observe all things, while 1 John asserts that knowing Him is contingent upon keeping His commandments.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
